        "subheading": "",
        "title": "<p>What is a Stone Shape?</p>",
        "description": "<p>Stone shape refers to the outline or silhouette of a gemstone when viewed from above. While often used interchangeably with “cut”, shape and cut have a distinct difference:<br/></p><ul><li>Shape describes the overall form (round, oval, pear)</li><li>Cut refers to how the facets are arranged to reflect light<br/></li></ul><p>Together, they define the personality of a stone.</p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
